This is the README for HTML::Valid version 0.06.

HTML::Valid is a "module" for the Perl computer programming language, a
library of computer code to install on a computer.  This document contains
four sections:

1. About - what the module does

2. Documentation - how to learn more about the module

3. Installation - how to install this module on a computer

4. Help - what to do if you get stuck

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

1. ABOUT

HTML::Valid - tidy/validate HTML

Validate/repair HTML. This module is based on "HTML Tidy", but not
on the Perl module "HTML::Tidy". However, you do not need to install
HTML Tidy before installing this, because the library is contained in
the distribution.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

2. DOCUMENTATION

You can read the documentation for the module online at the following
websites:

    * http://search.cpan.org/perldoc?HTML::Valid
    * http://metacpan.org/release/HTML-Valid

(These links go to the latest version of the module.)

After installing the module, you can read the documentation on your
computer using

    perldoc HTML::Valid

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

3. INSTALLATION

This module requires Perl version 5.6.1 or later.

To install the module from CPAN, use

    cpan HTML::Valid

If you have the App::cpanminus installer, you may prefer

    cpanm HTML::Valid

To install the module from the source file, HTML-Valid-0.06.tar.gz, follow
this sequence of commands:

    tar xfz HTML-Valid-0.06.tar.gz
    cd HTML-Valid-0.06
    perl Makefile.PL
    make
    make install

If you want to test the module before installing it, use "make test" after
"make" and before "make install".

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

4. HELP

To get help with the module, you can email the author, Ben Bullock, at
<bkb@cpan.org>. If you think there is a problem in the module, you can
report a bug at 

<https://github.com/benkasminbullock/html-valid/issues>,

or if you want to alter the source code of HTML::Valid, try the public
repository on github at 

<https://github.com/benkasminbullock/html-valid>. 

